---
import Deck from '../layouts/Deck.astro';
import AboutStakater from '../components/slides/AboutStakater.astro';
---
<Deck title="Stakater | Executive Overview" persona="VP / Regional Director">

  <!-- 1. About Stakater -->
  <AboutStakater />

  <!-- 2. The Problem -->
  <section class="section-light">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:900px;">
      <h1>
        Every Stalled OpenShift Account Is a<br/>
        <span class="highlight">Missed ARR Opportunity.</span>
      </h1>
      <br/><br/>
      <p style="font-size:24px; line-height:1.7; color:#1A0D32; max-width:100%;">
        Subscription sold. Cluster live.<br/>
        Nodes flat. No portfolio adoption.<br/>
        Renewal risk increasing.
      </p>
      <br/>
      <p style="font-size:24px; line-height:1.7; color:#1A0D32; max-width:100%;">
        The gap between installed and expanding<br/>
        is where ARR is being left on the table.
      </p>
      <br/><br/>
      <h2>
        Nobody in your current partner mix <span class="highlight">owns this gap.</span>
      </h2>
    </div>

    <aside class="notes">
      <p class="notes-dir">Pause after "Nobody owns this gap." Let it land.</p>
      <p class="notes-say">"This is the pattern across every market. The subscription closes. Implementation happens. Then nothing. Nodes stay flat. No new products. Renewal comes around and the customer asks what they got. The gap between installed and expanding — that's the ARR that's already been sold but never realized. And right now, no partner in your ecosystem is accountable for closing it."</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <!-- 3. What We Do -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h1 style="text-align:center;">
        We Convert <span class="highlight">Stalled Accounts</span> Into Growing Platforms.
      </h1>
      <br/><br/><br/>
      <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr); gap:60px; text-align:center;">

        <div>
          <div style="font-size:38px; font-weight:800; color:#FF5623; margin-bottom:16px;">More Nodes</div>
          <p style="font-size:18px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.6;">
            More workloads on OpenShift. ARR grows as the platform scales.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <div style="font-size:38px; font-weight:800; color:#FF5623; margin-bottom:16px;">More Products</div>
          <p style="font-size:18px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.6;">
            ODF, ACM, ACS, AMQ. We create the conditions for portfolio pull-through.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <div style="font-size:38px; font-weight:800; color:#FF5623; margin-bottom:16px;">More Clusters</div>
          <p style="font-size:18px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.6;">
            From one cluster to org-wide OpenShift standard. Multi-year, multi-site expansion.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <aside class="notes">
      <p class="notes-dir">Move quickly through the three columns. They're signposts, not detail slides.</p>
      <p class="notes-say">"Three vectors. More nodes — workloads expand, ARR scales. More products — we create the platform conditions that make ODF, ACM, ACS, AMQ adoption a natural next step. More clusters — we've taken single-cluster accounts to org-wide OpenShift standards. Each of those vectors is a revenue moment for Red Hat."</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <!-- 4. Proof -->
  <section class="section-light">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 style="text-align:center;">
        Three Accounts. <span class="highlight">Same Story.</span>
      </h1>
      <br/><br/><br/>
      <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr); gap:60px; text-align:center;">

        <div>
          <div style="margin-bottom:18px;">
            <img src="/logos/atg.png" alt="ATG" style="height:44px;">
          </div>
          <div style="font-size:40px; font-weight:800; color:#FF5623; margin-bottom:10px;">7 Years</div>
          <p style="font-size:18px; color:#1A0D32;">Sustained node growth. OpenShift became the strategic platform.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <div style="margin-bottom:18px;">
            <img src="/logos/csn.png" alt="CSN" style="height:44px;">
          </div>
          <div style="font-size:40px; font-weight:800; color:#FF5623; margin-bottom:10px;">ODF + Nodes</div>
          <p style="font-size:18px; color:#1A0D32;">Post-implementation gap closed. Storage and platform expansion followed.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <div style="margin-bottom:18px;">
            <img src="/logos/rs.png" alt="Region Skåne" style="height:44px;">
          </div>
          <div style="font-size:40px; font-weight:800; color:#FF5623; margin-bottom:10px;">1 → Many</div>
          <p style="font-size:18px; color:#1A0D32;">Single cluster to org-wide standard. New products adopted along the way.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <aside class="notes">
      <p class="notes-dir">Point to each logo. These are real accounts — use the names if the audience knows them.</p>
      <p class="notes-say">"Three accounts. ATG — seven consecutive years of node growth. That's not a project, that's a platform. CSN — we stepped in post-implementation and closed the gap. Nodes grew, ODF followed. Region Skåne — started with one cluster, now org-wide OpenShift standard. Same pattern every time: lifecycle ownership turns a stalled account into a growing one."</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <!-- 5. The Ask -->
  <section class="cta">
    <div class="container" style="text-align:center;">
      <h1>One Session.</h1>
      <br/><br/>
      <h2>
        We map 3–5 accounts from your portfolio<br/>
        against our lifecycle model.
      </h2>
      <br/>
      <h2>You see exactly where the ARR opportunity is.</h2>
      <br/><br/><br/>
      <h1 style="font-weight:800;">No Cost. No Commitment. Just the Map.</h1>
    </div>

    <aside class="notes">
      <p class="notes-dir">Slow down here. This is the close. Keep it clean.</p>
      <p class="notes-say">"The ask is simple. One working session. You bring three to five accounts — ones that are stalled, flat, or at renewal risk. We run them through our lifecycle model and show you exactly where the expansion opportunity sits. No cost. No commitment. You walk away with a map of ARR that's already in your portfolio, just not being realized yet. That's the conversation I'd like to have."</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

</Deck>
